        title = 'Light of Dawn',
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Lest We Forget'},
        next = {
            'The Dawn Also Rises',
            'A Forbidden Reunion',
        },
        requirements = {
            {name = 'See walkthrough for details.', count = 1},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. Enter Walk of Echoes for a cutscene.\n   - It does not matter from which area you enter. This flags the quest.\n2. Find 3 remnants of latent energy in the the same locations as 3 of the [Key Item] dawndrops from Fork in the Road:\n   - Beaucedine Glacier (S), there is an unlabeled (blank) point of interest at the bottom of the ramp down from the campaign warp on the border of G-9 and H-9. This gives you the temporary [Key Item] Breath of dawn.\n     - The C.A (Campaign Arbiter) Warp Beaucedine Glacier (S) is the fastest way.\n   - East Ronfaure (S), northwest corner of H-7 by a tree alongside the river. Use the Eastgate exit. Gives you a second [Key Item] Breath of dawn.\n   - Jugner Forest (S), southeast corner of Lake Mechieume at the border of H-6 and I-6. This gives you a third [Key Item] Breath of dawn.\n     - Survival Guide warp to East Ronfaure (S) then head east in Jugner Forest (S) is the fastest way for this step.\n3. Take these three Key Items to Walk of Echoes through the Grauberg (S) Veridical Conflux (F-5) or, if you\'ve opened it with Voidwatch quests, the Pashhow Marshlands (S) Veridical Conflux (J-9) close to survival guide teleport.\n   - Fastest way is through Rolanberry Fields entrance to Walk of Echoes via Lightsworm.\n   - The C.A (Campaign Arbiter) Warp Grauberg (S) will bring you closest to reach the Witchfire Glen Veridical Conflux at (F-5) if you have little to no progress with Voidwatch.\n4. Check the Ornate Door three times. Once for a cutscene, a second time for a shorter cutscene (introducing the fight), and a third time to begin the actual fight.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Chasing Shadows'] = {
        id = 60,
        start_npc = 'Rongelouts N Distaud',
        start_zone = 'Southern San d\'Oria (S)',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Disturbing rumors of the late Count Aurchiat\'s return from the grave have stirred disquiet among the Cardinal Stags. Hasten to their Xarcabard encampment and uncover the truth behind the ominous tidings.',
        reward = 'Darksteel Sheet',
        fame = 'Wings of the Goddess',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Blood of Heroes'},
        next = {'Face of the Future'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'You must wait one game day after completing Blood of Heroes in order to start this quest. You must also be on Wings of the Goddess Mission 38 (Note: mission name may be considered a spoiler).\n1. Speak to Rongelouts N Distaud in Southern San d\'Oria (S)  (I-9) for a cutscene to begin the quest.\n2. Zone in to Xarcabard (S) from Beaucedine Glacier (S) for a cutscene.\n   - The Beaucedine Glacier (S) Survival Guide places you next to the Xarcabard (S) entrance.\n3. Examine the Backfilled Pit in Xarcabard (S) at (F-8).\n   - West side of (F-8), lower level.\n4. Examine the Compact Footprint in the southeast corner of (H-8).\n5. Examine the Sunken Footprint at (H-6)/(H-7), up the ramp to the NW.\n6. Examine the Compact Footprint at (H-8) again.\n7. Zone into Batallia Downs (S) from Beaucedine Glacier (S) for a cutscene.\n   - Survival Guide to Batallia Downs → Cavernous Maw → Batallia Downs (S) → zone to Beaucedine Glacier (S) at (E-4) → zone back to Batallia Downs (S) is the shortest route distance wise.\n   - Survival Guide to Batallia Downs (S) → zone to Beaucedine Glacier (S) at (E-4) → zone back to Batallia Downs (S) is the route with the least zoning yet further away.\n8. Examine the Fresh Snowmelt in Batallia Downs (S) at (H-5) for a cutscene. (Left hand side before arriving at the Maw.)\n9. Examine the Fresh Snowmelt again to spawn an NM.\nYou have 30 minutes to defeat the Mannequin NM named Menechme.  You will be assisted by Excenmille.\n10. Menechme uses Polearm weaponskills, the most dangerous being Penta Thrust.\n11. Excenmille will occasionally use a skill called Stag\'s Cry that will give himself a temporary attack boost and magic attack bonus. Excenmille will also do several unique weaponskills such as Songbird Swoop, Gyre Strike, and Stag\'s Charge that do damage.\n12. You can win the BC fairly easily by simply curing Excenmille while avoiding getting hate on Menechme.\nOnce Menechme is defeated, examine the Fresh Snowmelt one last time for a cutscene and your reward.\n13. If your inventory is full, return to Batallia Downs (S) and examine the Fresh Snowmelt again to replay the cutscene and receive your reward.',
        notes = nil,
    },
