        id = 61,
        start_npc = 'Bostillette',
        start_zone = 'Batallia Downs (S)',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Your latest encounter with Zogbog has led to you being hurled through time. No sooner had you awakened in present day Vana\'diel than Iron Ram Engineer Bostillette appeared to entreat your aid. Make your way to base camp in the Jugner Forest if you would know more.',
        reward = 'Griffon Ring',
        fame = 'Wings of the Goddess',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = 'Fangmonger Forestaller',
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Chasing Shadows'},
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = 'This quest is started automatically after completing the previous quest, Chasing Shadows.\n1. Zone into Jugner Forest from Batallia Downs (present, not past) for a cutscene.\n2. Examine the Metallic Hodgepodge in Jugner Forest at (F-9) for a cutscene. (Located near the F-9/G-9 border, in the center of the grid at the base of a tree.)\n3. Zone into Ghelsba Outpost for a cutscene to receive the [Key Item] Orcish infiltration kit.\n   - Quick travel options:\n     - Teleport NPC Domenic in Lower Jeuno (J-7) will warp you there for 750 Gil if you have cleared Beyond Infinity.\n     - The Fort Ghelsba Survival Guide is right next to the zone.\n     - Use the Home Point to Yughott Grotto and cast Escape. This will leave you at the entrance to Ghelsba Outpost from West Ronfaure.\n   - Extra [Key Item] Orcish infiltration kits are available from Clandestine Marking at Ghelsba Outpost (I-10).\n4. Travel from Ghelsba Outpost to Map 1 of Yughott Grotto and examine the Scrape Mark at (G-9) for a cutscene.\n5. Examine the Scrape Mark again to enter the battlefield Face of the Future.\nYour opponents in this battlefield are a Fangmonger Colossus and 6 Tombstones, all statue type mobs. At the start of the battle, you will be assisted by Excenmille and Maxcimille.  Part way though the battle, Bostillette will join the fray.\n6. You only need to kill Fangmonger Colossus to win.\n7. Each Tombstone defeated will weaken the Colossus\' damage resistance.\n8. The Colossus and Tombstones use the weaponskills Seismostomp which does damage and Numbing Glare which is a conal paralysis move.  They all have very slow movement speed and can be easily kited. The enemy also seems to respawn a few as the fight continues.\n9. Kiting the statues while keeping the NPCs cured is a very easy way to win this battle, it has been won with three, two, and even one character in this manner.\nAfter the battle, examine the Cavernous Maw in Batallia Downs at (H-5) for a cutscene and to receive your reward.\n10. This Cavernous Maw must be unlocked in the past before the cutscene will play in the present day.\n11. Quickest way there is to use the Batallia Downs Survival Guide.\n12. If you have a full inventory at the time of the final cutscene, you will be prompted to examine a ??? near the maw in Batallia Downs (S) after you make space in your inventory to receive the Griffon Ring.\n13. You may now speak to Rholont in Southern San d\'Oria (S) to learn Trust Magic: Excenmille (S) if you possess the [Key Item] Bundle of half-inscribed scrolls.\nIf you are working on missions then return to Adieu, Lilisette.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Fire in the Hole'] = {
        id = 36,
        start_npc = 'Klara',
        start_zone = 'Bastok Markets',
        start_pos = 'H-6',
        description = 'Assist the Mythril Musketeers in their operation to destroy the siege turrets hidden inside the Ruhotz Silvermines.',
        reward = 'Republican Silver Medal',
        fame = 'Wings of the Goddess',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = 'Mythril Musketeer No. 6',
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Storm on the Horizon'},
        next = {'Quelling the Storm'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Zone into Bastok Markets (S) from North Gustaberg (S) for a cutscene that begins the quest. You will receive the [Key Item]Silvermine key.\n2. Go to North Gustaberg (S) top-middle of (E-9) and examine the Stonehoused Adit for a cutscene.\n   - Survival Guide or Allied Notes Teleport via Scarlette, C.A., Narkissa, C.A., or Wenonah, C.A. is fastest if you have access.\n3. Examine the Stonehoused Adit again to start the fight.\n   - If you fail this fight, you can get a new Silvermine key by speaking with Solitary Ant at North Gustaberg (S) (J-9).\n   - Notice: You must zone and wait a game day before getting a new key.\n4. Your goal is to protect the NPC as you run through a maze. At certain points Quadavs will attack the NPC.\n   - The NPC will follow the path marked below.\n     - See the Discussion tab for enemy attack patterns\n   - Occasionally the Quadavs will lose hate on whomever they are attacking and go after the NPC.\n   - You can cure the NPC via non-BLU spells and she can be buffed by most spells\nWARNING: This mission can not be completed solo without AoE sleep and/or damage. The Quadavs will kill the NPC long before you can target them all. It is advised to bring a 99 blm to use sleepga 2 along with whatever strong AoE damage spells you\'d like. If you bring whm sub you can use that to cast cure on the NPC in order to keep them alive. This is the quickest basic solution. Another alternative if at 99 is to use the Trust system, specifically Valaineral and his need of using Uriel Blade when engaging to decimate the Quadav horde, just be sure not to kill them in one shot else he won\'t engage properly.\n5. Multiple AOE sleeps is helpful depending on your recast times via Fast Cast\n6. The Quadavs don\'t come in all at once and come in staggered via multiple waves, so short cast, high damage AOEs, as well as multiple AOE sleeps is helpful (Subduction, Sheep Song, Dream Flower, etc.)\n7. Once you defeat all of the Quadavs, the battlefield will end once Adelheid reaches the turret.\n8. Enter Bastok Markets (S) from North Gustaberg (S) for a cutscene.\n9. Speak to Gentle Tiger in Bastok Markets (S) (H-6) for a cutscene.\n10. Speak to Gentle Tiger again for a second cutscene and to receive your reward.\nIf you are working on missions then return to In the Name of the Father.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Fires of Discontent'] = {
        id = 13,
        start_npc = 'Engelhart',
        start_zone = 'Bastok Markets',
        start_pos = 'K-10',
        description = 'Chairman Pale Eagle is planning to fan the growing fire of Galka',
        reward = '10,000 gil',
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Better Part of Valor'},
        next = {'Light in the Darkness'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Engelhart in Bastok Markets (S) at (K-10). You are tasked with finding information about a potential Galka uprising.\n2. Speak to Pagdako in Bastok Markets (S) at (H-9)\n3. Return to the present day Bastok Metalworks and speak with Iron Eater, inside the President\'s Office at (J-8). You may need to talk to him multiple times\n4. Return to the past and speak with Engelhart again.\n5. Now head to Grauberg (S) and find the ??? inside the cave at (I-6) for a cutscene.  The entrance to the cave is at (I-5), it\'s right on the border of H/I-5/6.\n6. After the cut-scene return to Bastok Markets (S) and speak with Engelhart again.\n7. Head towards where the Metalworks entrance would be in Bastok Markets (S) and speak with Gentle Tiger standing at the gate.\n8. Return to Engelhart and speak with him to complete the mission and receive your reward.',
        notes = '1. If continuing with Wings of the Goddess Missions, be sure to visit any of the Cavernous maws that you have unlocked outside Jeuno to activate the mission Cait Sith after completing this quest.\n2. Helpful Tip: If you set your homepoint to HP#1 in Bastok Markets (S) and use some form of warp, this counts as zoning.',
    },
