        next = {'Beneath the Mask'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Gentle Tiger in Bastok Markets (S) (H-6).\n2. Examine the ??? at Vunkerl Inlet (S) (F-6) for a cutscene.\n   - Located just east of the bridge\n   - Survival Guide in Vunkerl Inlet (S), or Atmacite Refiner are quickest ways.\n3. Examine the Beastman Ensign at Vunkerl Inlet (S) (J-7) for a cutscene.\n4. Return to Gentle Tiger to receive a [Key Item]Flare grenade.\n5. Return to the Beastman Ensign at Vunkerl Inlet (S) (J-7) for another cutscene.\n6. Examine the Beastman Ensign again to start a BC fight against an Arch Ahriman.\n   - This fight is easily won with lvl 99 and trusts.\n   - During the battle, the NM will vanish and a replica of Volker, Five Moons, or Nicolaus will appear in its stead.  When the replica is defeated, the Ahriman will reappear.\n   - In one battle the pattern was Arch Ahriman > Volker > Arch Ahriman > Five Moons > Arch Ahriman > Nicolaus > Arch Ahriman.\n   - The replicas use weapon skills based on their equipped weapons.  The Ahriman and Nicolaus replica will cast spells, including high-level AoE spells such as Sleepga II, Blindga, and Poisonga II.\n   - As of Jan 4, 2021, this battle can end after killing a single Arch Ahriman without fighting any replicas.\n7. Speak to Gentle Tiger for a cutscene and your reward.\n   - If you don\'t have the Elixir reward from Burden of Suspicion, this is another chance - keep this Elixir Tank for later use in The Truth Lies Hid.\nIf you are working on missions then return to Crossroads of Time.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Howl from the Heavens'] = {
        id = 54,
        start_npc = 'Robel-Akbel',
        start_zone = 'Windurst Waters (S)',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'As the battered Federation forces prepare to defend their city from the approaching hordes, the inscrutable Robel-Akbel schemes in his dark chambers. What terrible secrets lie behind his mask? Deliver the magicite he seeks, and long-sought truths just may be revealed...',
        reward = 'Cobra Staff',
        fame = 'Wings of the Goddess',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = 'The Moon\'s Companion',
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Sins of the Mothers'},
        next = {'Manifest Destiny'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Note: You need to wait a game day after completing Sins of the Mothers before you can activate this quest.\n2. Zone into Windurst Waters (S) from West Sarutabaruta (S) for a cutscene.\n3. Collect the Magicite from the three present day beastmen strongholds again (these may be done in any order):\n4. Make your way to Davoi.\n5. Head to (G-7) and click on the Wall of Dark Arts.\n6. Walk down the path into a large room and inspect the Magicite for the [Key Item]Shard of optistone.\n7. Enter Beadeaux from Pashhow Marshlands at (L-11).\n   - The fastest travel method is the Survival Guide warp to Beadeaux.\n8. Head back to the tunnel at (H-7) inside follow the left wall to zone into Qulun Dome.\n   - If you get a message that your silver bell, coruscant rosary, and black matinee necklace "glow faintly.", move closer to the door and try again until they "shine brightly!" and it opens.\n9. Examine the Magicite for the [Key Item]Shard of aurastone.\n10. Castle Oztroja is located at (L-8) in Meriphataud Mountains.\n   - The fastest travel method is the Survival Guide warp to Castle Oztroja.\n11. Enter and head to the door at (I-8).  You will see a lever at either side of the door.  One lever will open the door and the other will open a trap in the floor and cause you to fall into a pit. There is a very easy way to open this door.\n   - Stand between the two levers in front of the door.\n   - Trigger one of the levers and immediately run into the door. If done correctly, you should remain on the small edge in front of the door, even if the trapdoor opens. If that happens, just wait until it\'s closed again and try again with the other lever.\n12. On the second floor, head to (G-7) where you will exit into a courtyard.\n13. On this map, head north (without falling off) to a the corridor leading into the next map at (I-7).\n14. Here follow the right wall until you reach a door at (H-9).\n   - The mobs in this area are much higher level than the ones previously encountered.\n15. At the door light the torch and you will be taken through.\n16. Head South and take a right to another door. Click on the brass door to open it.  The zone is just ahead.\n17. Inside you will be in an area with no mobs. Examine the Magicite for the [Key Item]Shard of orastone.\n18. Once you have all three Magicite, return to Windurst Waters (S) and speak to Velda-Galda (K-9) for a cutscene.\n19. Zone into West Sarutabaruta (S) from Windurst Waters (S) for another cutscene.\n20. Examine the Windurstian Bulwark (J-8), located just ahead for a cutscene.\n21. Examine the Windurstian Bulwark to start a fight.\n   - This fight begins immediately and takes place on the field. Buff before examining.\n   - The time limit for this fight is 30 minutes and you are allowed to bring a full alliance of 18 people to this fight.\n   - Only the person initiating this fight needs to have the quest active.\n   - Killing the Tiny Lycopodiums before the fight makes targetting easier as they tend to follow you around.\n   - Clearing the Lycopodiums out with Area of Effect damage is recommended.\n   - Four waves of monsters will spawn and attempt to destroy the 3 Magical Barriers.\n     - Wave one is a group of 6 Yagudos: Yagudo Parivirs.\n     - Wave two is a group of 3 Taurus: Giganotaurs.\n     - Wave three is a group of 6 Demons Black Mages: Kindred Incantor.\n     - Wave four is a group of 3 Ahrimans: Blurry Eyes.\n   - Both Romaa Mihgo and at least one of the three Protective Wards must be kept alive.\n     - The Protective Wards cannot be Cured and they also take damage from AoE\'s.\n     - Curing Waltz can be used to heal the Protective Wards.\n   - If you fail the fight, you can zone and reinspect the Windurstian Bulwark to try again.\n22. Once you have finished the fight, before zoning examine the Windurstian Bulwark again for a long cutscene or you\'ll have to do the fight again.\n23. Zone into Windurst Waters (S) for the final cutscene and your reward.\nIf you are working on missions then return to Fate in Haze.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['In a Haze of Glory'] = {
        id = 38,
        start_npc = 'Diordinne',
        start_zone = 'Garlaige Citadel (S)',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Despite heightened security, the Garlaige Citadel has been infiltrated by an unseen enemy who is emitting poisonous gas with brutal results. Amidst the confusion, zealous new captain, Rahal, has ventured off on his own. Find him and ensure he does not come to harm.',
        reward = 'Fullmetal Bullet',
        fame = 'Wings of the Goddess',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Perils of the Griffon'},
        next = {'The Price of Valor'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Diordinne at (I-6) of the first map of Garlaige Citadel (S) will begin this quest.\n2. After the long cut-scene, he will give you the [Key Item] Number eight shelter key.\n3. Head east into the second map and go to (H-9) on the map and examine the Wooden Crates.\n4. Have the party leader examine the crates. Buffs wear upon entry.\n5. You will be transported to Ghoyu\'s Reverie and have 30 minutes to locate and kill the Orcish Turret.\n   - On Map 15 (where you spawn) in Ghoyu\'s Reverie, you can find the Orcish Turret by traveling all the way to the south around H-10 walking along the western walls.\n   - Be careful of the Goblin\'s Effluvial Grenade as the Noxious Spray will give nearby players a heavy poison effect.\n   - Effluvial Flasks have approximately 150HP and do not have to be destroyed.\n   - Other Orcs and Goblins do not have to be killed to win the battle though they have ~1500 HP and may sometimes get in the way.\n6. Upon defeating the Orcish Turret you will be transported out immediately and into another cutscene.\n   - Note: If you fail the BC, you will need to wait a game day to re-acquire the [Key Item] Number eight shelter key. You must return and speak with Diordinne to begin the game day wait for the KI.\n7. Head back to Southern San d\'Oria (S) and speak to Rholont (E-7) during nighttime hours (18:00 to 0:00 game time) to complete the quest and receive your reward.',
        notes = '1. Trivial at 99.\n2. Dancer sub job with Healing Waltz makes dealing with the Noxious Spray fairly easy.\n3. SMN75 + PLD75/DNC took 20 minutes easily.\nIf you are working on missions then return to In the Name of the Father.',
    },
    ['Knot Quite There'] = {
        id = 27,
        start_npc = 'Romaa Mihgo',
        start_zone = 'Windurst Waters',
        start_pos = 'G-11',
        description = 'Koru-Moru has set off to Jeuno with an inexperienced Mithran escort. Romaa wants you to make sure they arrive safely.',
        reward = 'Plt. Beastcoin',
        fame = 'Crystal War',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = 'No',
        previous = {'The Tigress Strikes'},
        next = {'A Manifest Problem'},
        requirements = {
            {name = '108-Knot Quipu', count = 1},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. Save time by first obtaining a 108-Knot Quipu first, which is dropped from Yagudo in Sauromugue Champaign (S) or nearby \'Banishing Gate 2\' in Garlaige Citadel (S).\n   - A good farming spot is inside the fortification at (K-9) just north of a Survival Guide.\n   - There are also other Yagudo and fortifications to the north of (K-9).\n2. Talk to Dhea Prandoleh in Windurst Waters (S) (H-10). She should say something about the Boss having her eyes on you.\n3. Start the quest by clicking on the (left side) Door: Acolyte Hostel in (K-5) of Windurst Waters (S) for a cutscene involving the younger version of Ajido-Marujido.\n4. Go to Sauromugue Champaign (S) (F-6) and click on the Bulwark Gate where the zone to Jeuno would normally be for the next cutscene.\n5. Trade the 108-Knot Quipu you should\'ve obtained in the first step here to the Bulwark Gate for another cutscene with Rachemace.\n6. Click the Bulwark Gate for another cutscene with Rachemace.\n   - \'\'NOTE: Click the Bulwark Gate until you trigger every possible cutscene you can get here, when it says "the door is firmly sealed" at least 3 times in a row then proceed just to be sure.\n7. Zone into Southern San d\'Oria (S) from East Ronfaure (S) for a cutscene with Pattna-Ottna.\n   - \'\'NOTE: If you are mounted when entering Southern San d\'Oria (S) from East Ronfaure (S), you will not receive this cutscene. Exit back out and re-enter on foot to trigger the cutscene.\n   - The Atmacite Refiner at the gate can Voidwatch warp to East Ronfaure right at the zone-line if you\'re over level 75.\n     - If you haven\'t done any Voidwatch content, you will not be able to utilize the Atmacite Refiner whatsoever, regardless of level.\n8. Go past the Portcullis (gate) and click on the first Door: House on the right at (M-8) in Southern San d\'Oria (S) for the final cutscene with Joseaneaut and your reward.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Light in the Darkness'] = {
        id = 19,
        start_npc = 'Gentle Tiger',
        start_zone = 'Bastok Markets',
        start_pos = 'H-6',
        description = 'Gentle Tiger has been tirelessly watching the entrance to the Metalworks. How did Pagdako manage to sneak past him...?',
        reward = 'Adaman Ingot',
        fame = 'Crystal War',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Fires of Discontent'},
        next = {'Burden of Suspicion'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Gentle Tiger in Bastok Markets (S) (H-6) for a cutscene that begins the quest.\n   - Gentle Tiger may first remark upon a Bundle of half-inscribed scrolls, speak with him again to receive the cutscene.\n2. Speak to Pagdako at (H-9) for some dialogue.\n3. Speak to Blatherix at (F-8).  Trade him 30 Gob. Chocolate or 5,000 gil  to receive a [Key Item]Mine shaft key\n   - Gob. Chocolate is sold by Pawkrix in Lower Jeuno (H-10).\n4. Zone in to Pashhow Marshlands (S) from Grauberg (S) for a brief cutscene.\n   - Survival Guide to Grauberg (S) is quickest way.\n   - Voidwatch teleport from an Atmacite Refiner in the past to Pashhow Marshlands (S) will also put you at the Grauberg (S) zone line.\n5. Examine the Corroded Door in Pashhow Marshlands (S) (F-5) to enter a battlefield.\n6. In the battlefield, you will encounter x1 Sapphire Quadav and x10 Sapphirine Quadav.\n   - Trusts may be used in this fight.\n   - Any job in item level 119 gear should have no issue clearing this fight.\n   - It is best to defeat six of the Sapphirine Quadavs first, as defeating the Sapphire Quadav will cause the Sapphirine Quadavs to scatter around the map.\n   - Defeating enough Quadav will clear the mission, returning you back to Pashhow Marshlands (S).\nNotice: If for any reason your inventory is full before starting this next step below then you will not obtain the reward and you will have to rewatch the entire cutscene, choice selections included.\n7. Speak to Gentle Tiger for a cutscene. In it, you are given the opportunity to answer questions. You can choose again if you answer incorrectly, but these are the correct answers:\n   - "...the ventilation shaft."\n   - "...the senator did not light the lantern."\n   - "...he was distracted."\n8. When the cutscene ends you will receive your reward.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Lost in Translocation'] = {
        id = 0,
        start_npc = 'Thorben',
        start_zone = 'Batallia Downs',
        start_pos = 'J-10',
        description = 'Thorben has dropped his squad\'s map of Grauberg  somewhere in Eldieme Necropolis. Find the map and return it to him.',
        reward = 'Map of Grauberg (If you do not already own it)\n2,000 Experience Points\n2,000 Gil',
        fame = nil,
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Speak with Thorben in Batallia Downs (S) at (J-10).\n2. Enter The Eldieme Necropolis (S) via the Crypt Door next to Thorben.\n3. There are three pieces to the map.\n   - The [Key Item] Right map piece is located at (I-9) (click the Sarcophagus)\n   - The [Key Item] Middle map piece is located at (H-8) (click the Gravestone)\n   - The [Key Item] Left map piece is located at (H-7).  This piece is given by an NPC Erik who is now present during Campaign as per the 11/26/07 patch.\n4. After you receive the final map piece; Select the Blank Target (the brazier, next to Erik at (H-7)) and select "Into the fire". This will warp you back out to Batallia Downs (S) - (J-10).\n5. Speak to Thorben again for a cutscene.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Manifest Destiny'] = {
        id = 62,
        start_npc = 'Dhea Prandoleh',
        start_zone = 'Windurst Waters (S)',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Having successfully turned back the Yagudo offensive, Lehko Habhoka and the Mithran mercenaries strike for Castle Oztroja to finish off their foe. The final conflict is nigh--report to the mercenary camp in the Meriphataud Mountains without delay!',
        reward = 'Hi-Reraiser',
        fame = 'Wings of the Goddess',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Howl from the Heavens'},
        next = {'At Journey\'s End'},
        requirements = {
            {name = 'Dorter Key', count = 3},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Dhea Prandoleh for a cutscene.\n2. Examine the Mithran Bivouac in Meriphataud Mountains (S) (I-8) for another cutscene.\n   - This is just NE of the Recall-Meriph telepoint.\n3. Enter Castle Oztroja (S) for a cutscene.\n4. Farm three Dorter Keys, which drop from Yagudo Eradicators, Yagudo Knights Templar, Yagudo Prioresses, and Yagudo Prelates found in Meriphataud Mountains (S) and inside Castle Oztroja (S).\n   - You will need this for all characters that wish to complete this mission.\n5. Click the Iron Grilles located in the outside areas of the second floor of the castle (see maps) until you receive a message stating that you sense someone on the other side.\n6. Trade the Dorter Keys to three of the Iron Grilles with prisoners trapped inside.\n   - Each key is lost when trading, so be sure to examine the Grille before hand. If you trade the key to an empty cell you will not get a cutscene, and the key will be lost.\n   - Quest progress for freeing prisoners does not count towards other party member\'s progress.\n     - There are two outdoor areas that hold prison cells. One located at E-7 and another at G-9\n7. After freeing three sets of prisoners, you will obtain a [Key Item]Poet god\'s key after the third cutscene.\n8. Head to the top of Castle Oztroja (S) and check the Collapsing Floor for a cutscene.\n9. Examine the Collapsing Floor again to enter a BCNM.\n10. The fight is against Tzee Xicu the Manifest and 2x Air Elementals.\n   - Elementals cast Aeroga, Aeroga II, Silence, and Gravity\n   - Tzee Xicu can use special TP move Kamitachi (full dispel and high damage, hate reset).\n11. Defeat Tzee Xicu the Manifest to continue.\n   - If you lose the fight, you must return to the Mithran Bivouac to re-obtain the [Key Item]Poet god\'s key.\n   - If you win the fight but have a Hi-Reraiser in your inventory, you will be asked to pick up your reward at the Mithran Bivouac.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Message on the Wind'] = {
        id = 1,
        start_npc = 'Romualdo',
        start_zone = 'Batallia Downs (S)',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Romualdo believes he has heard the voice of his deceased father in Grauberg. He\'d like to head there again to find out for sure, but is unable to leave his post...',
        reward = 'Smart Grenade',
        fame = 'Crystal War',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = 'Windtalker',
        repeatable = 'No',
        previous = nil,
        next = nil,
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Romualdo, (K-9) Metalworks in the present.\n   - The quest doesn\'t appear in your log until the next step.\n2. Go to the past, and speak to Romualdo in Batallia Downs (S), (I-7).  (On top of a hill just past the Rampart Gate.)\n   - (Optional) Speak to Romualdo again for additional text.\n3. Talk to Childerich at (E-12) by the Old Cabin in Grauberg (S).\n   - (Optional) Speak to Childerich again for addition text.\n4. Examine the ??? at (J-9) to the east of the Grauberg Guntower.\n5. Speak to Childerich.\n   - (Optional) Speak to Childerich again for addition text.\n6. Speak to Romualdo in Batallia Downs (S) to complete the quest and receive your reward.\n   - (Optional) Speak to Romualdo again for additional text.\nSome post-quest cutscenes are available that award the proper title.\n7. Speak to Romualdo in present.\n8. Speak to Childerich and chose the option "Message on the Wind" to get the title.\n      - You can select the other options for optional text without affecting the quest outcome.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['No Rest for the Weary'] = {
        id = 88,
        start_npc = 'Voidwatch Officer',
        start_zone = nil,
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Mission Orders: No sooner has one threat been quelled than another emerges. You have been granted a brief respite, but cannot help but feel concern at the state of the Voidwatch effort in the Crystal War era...',
        reward = 'White stratum abyssite VI, Starlight Voidwatcher\'s emblem',
        fame = 'Wings of the Goddess',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'A New Menace'},
        next = {'A World in Flux'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Speak with any Voidwatch Officer in a Shadowreign (S) area to receive a Voidwatch alarum.\n   - If you have not previously returned to the Bulwark Gate in Sauromugue Champaign (S), the Voidwatch Officer will not give you the alarum. You must first receive a cutscene there which will reward you with 30,000 gil. You must wait until the next game day and zone after receiving this cutscene, then speak with a Voidwatch Officer to activate the quest.  Voidwatch Officer MUST be from the Shadowreign era.\n2. Proceed to the Bulwark Gate (F-6) in Sauromugue Champaign (S) for a cutscene.\n   - VW Warp to Sauromugue Champaign (S) is the quickest way to get there.\n   - At the end of the cutscene, the key items White stratum abyssite VI and Starlight Voidwatcher\'s emblem will be received, the quest will be completed, and the next quest will be automatically flagged.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['On Sabbatical'] = {
        id = 32,
        start_npc = 'Erlene & Ulbrecht',
        start_zone = 'Batallia Downs (S)',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Prof. Schultz, founder of the seminal Schultz School of Martial Theory, has vanished. Set out and find the missing professor to set Erlene\'s mind at ease, and to deliver Ulbrecht\'s message.',
        reward = 'Klimaform (Scroll)',
        fame = 'Crystal War',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'A Little Knowledge'},
        next = {'Downward Helix'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Speak to Erlene in The Eldieme Necropolis (S) at (J-8) to begin quest. You will be given [Key Item] Ulbrecht\'s sealed letter.\n2. Speak to Gentle Tiger in Bastok Markets (S) at (H-6) for a cutscene.\n      - You may need to speak to him twice. If he mentions that he has never heard of a bundle of half-inscribed scrolls then you will need to speak to him again.\n3. Travel to the SW corner of Pashhow Marshlands (S) to touch the Indescript Markings targetable location, on the grid line between (E-11) and (E-10) for a cutscene. You will obtain [Key Item] Schultz\'s sealed letter.\n   - There are level ~80 Virulent Peistes around the Indescript Markings that aggro on sight.\n     - Either come with Invisible handy and wait until they turn, or defeat them with a high enough leveled job.\n4. Return to Erlene for your Klimaform Schema.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Perils of the Griffon'] = {
        id = 37,
        start_npc = 'Rholont',
        start_zone = 'Southern San d\'Oria',
        start_pos = 'E-7',
        description = 'As if the threat of disbandment was not enough, the Young Griffons must also fend off a determined Captain Rongelouts from confiscating their Orcish warmachine. Assist them in the desperate defense of their base!',
        reward = 'Elixir',
        fame = 'Wings of the Goddess',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = 'Knight of the Swiftwing Griffon',
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Wrath of the Griffon'},
        next = {'In a Haze of Glory'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. You must zone and wait one game day after completing Wrath of the Griffon in order to start this quest.\n2. Speak to Rholont (E-7) in Southern San d\'Oria (S) to initiate the quest.\n3. Zone out and speak to Rholont again for another cutscene.\n4. Speak to Daigraffeaux at (I-11) (his location in the past is where the chocobo stables are located in present San d\'Oria).\n5. Back to Rholont for another cutscene.\n6. Head to Jugner Forest (S) at (I-6) (East side of the river) and examine the ??? tree stump to receive the [Key Item]Orcish warmachine body.\n   - The shortest path is via the East Ronfaure (S) survival guide.\n7. Return to Southern San d\'Oria (S) and speak to Rholont complete the quest with your reward.',
        notes = nil,
    },
    ['Provenance'] = {
        id = 95,
        start_npc = nil,
        start_zone = 'Provenance',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Mission Orders: A place from which all radiance once shone brightly forth now dimly flickers on the brink of existence... It is here that the source of Vana\'diel\'s suffering dwells, say the now multifarious caits.',
        reward = nil,
        fame = 'Wings of the Goddess',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = nil,
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Brace for the Unknown'},
        next = {'Crystal Guardian'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Obtain the following three key items:\n   - Beguiling petrifact\n     - Obtained for 330,000 cruor from a Voidwatch officer, rarely from any Zilart, City, or Jeuno path Voidwatch battle, or guaranteed from Beguiling Radiance.\n   - Seductive petrifact\n     - Obtained for 330,000 cruor from a Voidwatch officer, rarely from any Tavnazia, City, or Jeuno path Voidwatch battle, or guaranteed from Seductive Radiance.\n   - Maddening petrifact\n     - Obtained for 330,000 cruor from a Voidwatch officer, rarely from any Aht Urhgan, City, or Jeuno path Voidwatch battle, or guaranteed from Maddening Radiance.\n2. After obtaining one of the petrifacts, examine the Regal Pawprints in Provenance for a cutscene.\n3. With two in possession, examine the Regal Pawprints in Provenance for another cutscene.\n4. Return to the Regal Pawprints with all three in possession for one final cutscene (there will be three cutscenes if you did not watch the previous cutscenes after obtaining each KI petrifact).\n5. Examine the Provenance Protocrystal for a brief cutscene which completes the quest and begins the next quest automatically.',
        notes = nil,
    },
