    ['Seeing Blood-red'] = {
        id = 34,
        start_npc = 'Erlene',
        start_zone = 'Batallia Downs (S)',
        start_pos = nil,
        description = 'Ulbrecht\'s maniacal machinations have been made clear, and only one person holds the key to tracking him down. Find Professor Schultz!',
        reward = 'Scholar\'s M.board',
        fame = 'Crystal War',
        fame_level = nil,
        title = 'Summa Cum Laude',
        repeatable = nil,
        previous = {'Downward Helix'},
        next = {'Survival of the Wisest'},
        requirements = nil,
        walkthrough = '1. Wait until the next game day and zone after completing the previous quest in order to begin this one.\n2. Speak to Erlene, The Eldieme Necropolis (S) (J-8) on Scholar. She will ask you to return to the previous location where you found Schultz.\n   - (Optional) Speaking with her again will result in some additional dialogue.\n   - After flagging the quest with this cutscene, you can continue forward through the rest of it on any job.\n3. Travel to the Indescript Markings in Pashhow Marshlands (S) along the north edge of (E-11) next to the wall for the [Key Item] Unaddressed sealed letter.\n   - The Recall-Pashh telepoint and Survival Guide will take you to the southern end of the map, leaving you with a shorter walk West than using the Campaign Arbiters warp NPCs from a Shadowreign city. The Grauberg (S) Survival Guide isn\'t terribly far from it, either.\n4. Read the Unaddressed sealed letter by examining it in your Temporary Key Item menu.\n5. Return to Erlene and talk to her again for a cutscene and a [Key Item] Porting magic transcript.\n6. Go to Grauberg (S) (E-10) and enter the cave opposite the waterfall. Examine the unnamed shimmering light on the ground.\n   - The cave entrance is on the boundary line of E-10 and F-10. If you go near the waterfall, you\'ve gone too far. The entrance to the cave is on dry land. Also, if you don\'t heed this advice and still go past the waterfall, you will have to go all the way back around.\n   - Using the Campaign Arbiters warp NPCs from a Shadowreign city is the closest arrival point. The Grauberg (S) Survival Guide is a bit further away.\n7. Inspect the Indescript Marking on the wall in the same cave to enter the instance.\n   - Only the party leader with the quest active can enter the party into the instance, which is held in Ruhotz Silvermines.\n   - If you fail this fight, you will need to trade Erlene a Sheet of Vellum to receive another Porting magic transcript before re-entering the fight.\n8. Return to Erlene after clearing the battlefield for your reward.',
        notes = '1. Added in the March 2008 Version Update.\n2. Since the October 2016 Version Update, players were able to summon Trusts.',
    },
